Nigerian-Chinese Group Plans Ethanol Refineries, Guardian Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-07-27T08:35:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/nigerian-chinese-group-plans-ethanol-refineries-guardian-reports.html
Global Biofuels Ltd. , a Nigerian
energy company, in partnership with  Hong Kong ’s COZA
International Ltd. and  China ’s WEMET International Complete
Plant Engineering Co., plans to spend $183 million on ethanol
refining plants in West Africa,  The Guardian  reported.  The first phase of the project will start in the third
quarter in  Nigeria ’s southwestern Ekiti State, Managing Director
Felix Obada told the Lagos-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 